## 4. Concepts locked in at this milestone

- Declarative vs imperative operations: describe the end state, let the tool derive the steps
- Service discovery by name via compose DNS; single-exposed-port topology
- depends_on + service_healthy as startup choreography; healthchecks as load-bearing signals
- Liveness vs readiness; why shallow checks are a deliberate choice
- Graceful degradation; request failure vs service failure vs container failure
- Signals: SIGTERM vs SIGKILL; exit code arithmetic (128 + signal)
- Restart policy semantics: operator intent vs unexplained death; unless-stopped as the sane default
- Resource limits as failure isolation
- .env / .env.example discipline: document exactly what the environment must supply

